  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\">\n<div class=\"fr-view\">\n<h1><strong>Introduce yourself in Flip</strong></h1>\n<p>This is your only chance to use English to introduce yourself to the other teachers and students, but from tomorrow on you will have to use Japanese!</p>\n<div class=\"fr-view\"><p>Please go on Flip and follow these instructions:</p></div>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Click the Flip link and sign in.<br></span></strong><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Go to Flip</span></span> </span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma,Geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><a href=\"https://flipgrid.com/2eee561c\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> and click on<span style=\"font-family: Tahoma,Geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">\"<strong>Join with your guest password</strong>\", <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma,Geneva,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">getting started with the\"Introduce yourself\" lesson.</span></span></span> Your Flip password is <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>GGNnek0#</strong></span></span><strong>.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Record your video!<br></strong>Tap the green plus sign to begin recording your response. To submit your video response, follow these steps: record your video, review + edit, take a selfie,<strong> </strong>type your email address, then submit! You don't have to show your face if you don't want to. You can cover it with an emoji, when you record your video, use\"pixel mode\" or just hide it ;)</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-07-22_at_11.40.11.png\" style=\"width: 482px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" srcset=\"../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-07-22_at_11.40.11.png?width=1920 1x, ../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-07-22_at_11.40.11.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, ../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-07-22_at_11.40.11.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></span></span></p>\n<span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Remember to always attach the text version of your message (<strong>in the caption box</strong>), for the teachers to check. You can see the teacher's video reply from <a href=\"https://auth.flipgrid.com/signin?redirect_url=https://my.flipgrid.com/me\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">my.flipgrid.com</a> page.</span></span>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">You can also write your script in the sticky note on the top right of your video, before submitting it. It helps you remember what to say in your video.</span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-05-13_at_12.33.42.png\" style=\"width: 431px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" srcset=\"../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-05-13_at_12.33.42.png?width=1920 1x, ../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-05-13_at_12.33.42.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, ../../images/shared/Screen_Shot_2022-05-13_at_12.33.42.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Don't forget to add your script in the caption to all the video messages as part of the Flip assignments!</strong></span></span></p>\n<p>You can find your videos in the\"Activity\" section on <span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><a href=\"https://auth.flipgrid.com/signin?redirect_url=https://my.flipgrid.com/me\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">my.flipgrid.com</a> page.</span></span></p>\n<p>　<a href=\"https://flipgrid.com/2eee561c\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"../../images/shared/Flip_correction-EN.png\" style=\"width: 272px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" srcset=\"../../images/shared/Flip_correction-EN.png?width=1920 1x, ../../images/shared/Flip_correction-EN.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, ../../images/shared/Flip_correction-EN.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"></span><br></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">What is Flip?</span></strong></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Flip is a free, simple way to foster short video-based discussions on classroom topics. Here you can interact with your teacher and your fellow classmates, sharing short videos and practicing your Japanese speaking skills. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">A teacher will review your video by leaving a video message for you. Please reply to the video message by creating your own Flip video response. We recommend you <strong>check and respond to all messages</strong> to optimise your learning.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Watch this introduction video for more details:</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fr-video fr-fvc fr-dvb\"><iframe src=\"https://platform.thinkific.com/videoproxy/v1/play/bq5u65mhra84otn6bbng\" scrolling=\"no\" class=\"videoproxy_embed\" title=\"Getting Started Students (1).mp4 - 00:48\" name=\"videoproxy_embed\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></span></p>\n</div>",
